This paper deals with wireless communication networks and interference modeling, which are topics that fall under the category of Networked and Distributed Systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of antennas and backhauling, which are related to Information Theory (cs.IT) and Multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of interference, which is a concern in the field of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper proposes a solution for coexistence between different communication systems, which is a topic in the field of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
